  "session_header": "[SESSION_HEADER]\nTimestamp: 1492 DR, Hammer 1, 00:15:00\nLocation: Ruined Observatory\nStatus: Lvl 1 Ranger | HP: 12/12 | XP: 0/300",
  "resources": "HD: 1/1, Spells: No Spells Yet (Level 2+), Potions: 0/0, Exhaustion: 0",
  "narrative": "You pause and let your eyes wander across the ruined observatory, letting them adjust to the darkness between lightning flashes.\n\n**The Interior:** Above you, the partial dome of the observatory still holds—cracked and weathered, but intact enough to provide shelter from the worst of the rain. Ancient brass instruments, now corroded and useless, litter the floor around a central pedestal. A collapsed spiral staircase leads to upper levels now accessible only by climbing the crumbling stone steps. Water stains on the walls tell stories of countless storms like this one.\n\n**The Entrance:** The main archway where you stand faces south—a natural path from the settlements. The stone threshold is worn smooth, suggesting others have sought shelter here before you. Fresh boot prints in the dust? No—too wet washed, away by the rain.\n\n**The Windows:** Several arrow slits around the circumference offer vantage points. Through the largest, you can see the tree line to the north—where that flash of movement caught your eye. The rain makes it impossible to see clearly, but something is out there.\n\n**Above:** Through gaps in the dome, you catch glimpses of the storm clouds churning. The wind whistles through these openings with an almost melodic quality—like distant warning cries.",
  "planning_block": {
    "thinking": "The observatory offers good defensive positions, but that movement in the tree line troubles me. I need to decide whether to investigate further or maintain my position here.",
    "choices": {
      "watch_north_window": {
        "text": "Watch the Northern Window",
        "description": "Position yourself at the arrow slit facing the tree line to monitor for movement.",
        "pros": ["Direct view of the area where movement was spotted", "Stays dry"],
        "cons": ["Limited field of view", "Static position"],
        "risk_level": "low",
